%{EXT-COMMENTS
Extension to allocate setup costs over simulated quantity instead of average lot size
- Assumes simulated costs are for single manufacturing run with single setup (customized orders)
- Developed for Screen Graphics to meet estimating requirements for customized customer orders
  of varying qunatities

Step #1: Add quickLink section to show table of possible prices for quote/estimating
Table of form:

Unit  Setup	 Target  Qty   
Cost  Cost   Margin         500   1000  5000  10000  20000 
1.23  500.00  15%           2.57  1.99  ...
1.23  500.00  20%           2.68  ...
...

Allow for user input for 5 qty buckets and 5 margin buckets with recalc; 
Initial defaults for all buckets set by system;

Calculations:
Unit Cost  = 

Setup Cost = sum of [Standard Setup Hours (WRKRTM.WKSUHR) * Standard Setup Rate (WRKRTM.WKSLR)]
                over all routing steps in the simulation (WRKRTM.WKXHND = current hex handle)

Target Margin is input value [default from 25% to 55% in 5% increments per SG]

Qty is input value [default to 1000, 2500, 5000, 7500, 10000 per SG]

Price = (Unit Cost + (Setup Cost / Qty)) * (1 + Target Margin)

**** MUST ADD QUICKLINK TO THE QUICKLINKS IN THE CPP CONFIGURATION ****
D2W Name            CostSimulatorDisplay.d2w
Quick Link          estimator
Description         Estimator
Rows to Display     99999
Image
Class
URL ID
Reserved Record on Update

**** MUST ADD QUICKLINK TO APPROPRIATE ROLE IN THE CPP CONFIGURATION ****
Edit the CostSimulatorDisplay.d2w entry for the appropriate role, add Estimator quickLink

%}

